{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013NS5cx9LLhR6g2DawuEZej","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Elasticsearch pod is running but DNS for `es-1.es-headless` can't resolve (because es-1 and es-2 haven't started yet - the StatefulSet starts pods sequentially and they won't start until es-0 is Ready). This is a chicken-and-egg problem: es-0 needs to become Ready before es-1 starts.\n\nThe main issues are:\n1. The readiness probe has a 1s timeout which is too short for the curl command\n2. The pods can't start sequentially because es-0 readiness probe fails\n\nLet me fix the readiness probe:\n- Add `timeoutSeconds: 5` to the readiness probe\n- Switch to a simpler TCP socket check with netcat to verify port 9200 is open, which should be faster and more reliable for the initial startup phase\n\nThe real bottleneck is the readiness probe timing out on es-0, which blocks the entire StatefulSet from progressing. DNS resolution errors in the logs are just warnings since the seed host discovery retries automatically. I need to increase the `timeoutSeconds` on the readiness probe to give Elasticsearch enough time to respond, or alternatively use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to spin up all pods simultaneously so DNS entries exist from the start.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1043,"cache_read_input_tokens":32166,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1043},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be64813d-0120-4c22-9f62-37e5510975fc","uuid":"f217f06f-7ee1-48f8-927d-2fd102b6853b","request_id":"req_011CcQQrLNunZMMTtb2DCkuD"}
